4.title: What is Flo Edge
4.content: Flo Edge is a compute, sensor & comms platform for ai and robotics application.

5.title: Specifications:
5.content: Compute and memory . | Chipset | Qualcomm Snapdragon 845 (10 nm) | . | Architecture | 64 bit | . | CPU | Octa-core (4x2.8 GHz Kryo 385 Gold & 4x1.8 GHz Kryo 385 Silver) | . | GPU | Qualcomm Adreno 630 | . | DSP | Qualcomm Hexagon 685 | . | RAM | 6GB | . | Storage | 128GB (UFS 2.1) | . Sensors and others . | Cameras | 12 MP f/1.9 1/2.55 1.4µm dual pixel PDAF | . | IMU | 9 axis (accelerometrt + gyroscope + magnetometer) | . | GNSS | GLONASS, Beidou, GPS, QZSS, Galileo | . | Misc | Yes | . | Sound | Yes | . Comms . | Network | GSM/HSPA/LTE | . | WLAN | Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct, DLNA | . | USB | USB Type-C 2.0, OTG | . Software . | OS | Debian 10 (Buster) | . 6.title: Flo Edge Attachment
6.content: Attachment for ease of use of Flo Edge .

9.title: Turning on
9.content: . | Connect power source. | Led on Flo Edge attachment will start blinking red. | When led becomes solid green Flo Edge is up and running. | Connect to Flo Edge hostpot (ssid: “FloEdge”, password: “FloEdge”) | ssh to Flo Edge using cmd {ssh root@192.168.43.1 -p 2222} | Now you are in a preconfigure debian OS for robotics and ai application. | .

10.title: Turning off
10.content: . | Long press the power button on Flo Edge attachment | Led on Flo Edge attachment will start blinking green. | When Flo Edge is turned off led will become solid red. | .
